'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH FSCK.KAFS 8 "2026-03-01" "kafs 0.2.2" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
fsck.kafs \- check and repair specific KAFS consistency layers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fsck.kafs
.RB [ --check-journal ]
.RB [ --repair-journal-reset ]
.RB [ --repair-dirent-ino-orphans ]
.I image
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fsck.kafs
validates and optionally repairs selected consistency layers.
By default it validates the in-image journal (header and record CRCs).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --check-journal
Validate the journal layer and exit (default behavior).
.TP
.B --repair-journal-reset
When journal validation fails, reset the journal ring safely offline
(zero data and rewrite header).
.TP
.B --repair-dirent-ino-orphans
Repair the dirent->ino layer by reclaiming orphan inodes
(inodes with link count 0) and releasing their referenced blocks via HRL.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Validation/repair completed successfully.
.TP
.B 3
Journal validation failed.
.TP
.B 4
Journal reset operation failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mkfs.kafs (8),
.BR kafs (1)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
